Refer the below document for setting up KIND clusters for peering and setting peering between them before we proceed with usage of exported services in peering setup:-
https://github.com/abhineet-1987/Abhineet/blob/main/Consul/Kubernetes/KIND/PodToPodCommunication-MultiCluster
https://github.com/abhineet-1987/Abhineet/tree/main/Consul/Peering/Kubernetes/control-plane-peering

Steps:-
Deploy static-client app static-client.yaml in cluster-01. "kubectl appy -f static-client.yaml"
Deploy static-server app static-server.yaml in cluster-02. "kubectl appy -f static-server.yaml"
Deploy ExportedServices CRD into cluster-02. "kubectl appy -f exported.yaml"
Deploy ServiceIntentions CRD into cluster-02 if ACLs are enabled else not required. "kubectl appy -f intentions.yaml"
